`,r.jsx(n.p,{children:"That extra freedom is what makes agents useful. It is also what makes them risky. A model that can choose actions needs boundaries, state, observability, and a clear runtime contract. Otherwise you have a demo that looks smart until it hits the first ambiguous request."}),`
`,r.jsx(n.p,{children:"This post is a plain-English map of the pieces."}),`
`,r.jsx(n.h2,{id:"agent-workflow-and-assistant",children:r.jsx(n.a,{href:"#agent-workflow-and-assistant",children:"Agent, workflow, and assistant"})}),`
`,r.jsx(n.p,{children:'The word "agent" gets used loosely, so it helps to separate three related ideas.'}),`
